Option 2: Iterating backward starting from `1`. In this case, the loop starts from `1` and iterates up to `10`, printing elements from the end of the list with a decreasing index.

These changes can be useful in scenarios where you need to reverse the order of elements or access elements in a different sequence. Choose the option that best fits your specific requirements.

